Last Update Instructions – RTX Housing

This update is primarily focused on performance improvements and stability fixes. A large amount of additional debug logging has been added to help identify issues more easily and prevent crashes, timeouts, and data inconsistencies.

This version was mainly developed and optimized for very large servers with hundreds of players. It is designed to handle a high number of houses, furniture, and active players without performance issues. With these changes, we guarantee stable behavior even under heavy load.

All previously known issues have been addressed in this version.

We are also currently working on a major upcoming update that will introduce new features and further improvements.

Installation Instructions

1. Replace the entire rtx_housing resource with the new version.
   Do not merge files. A full replacement is required to ensure everything works correctly.

2. Config folder:
   You may keep your existing config folder.

3. HTML folder:
   You can keep your entire html folder without any changes.

Additional Notes

* This update includes multiple performance optimizations, especially around furniture handling, events, and database usage.
* Debug messages have been significantly expanded. These will help track down issues if anything goes wrong.
* The system is now more resistant to spam, race conditions, and heavy usage scenarios.

Important Recommendation

After installing:

* Restart your server completely (not just the resource)

This update is designed to be more stable, scalable, and production-ready for high population servers.
